{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/fxXkKpMVPSJSdciQStPEEdC0nnj.jpg","belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[{"id":18,"name":"Drama"}],"homepage":"","id":149136,"imdb_id":"tt0065948","origin_country":["PL"],"original_language":"pl","original_title":"Krajobraz po bitwie","overview":"Film opens with the mad rush of haphazard freedom as the concentration camps are liberated. Men are trying to grab food, change clothes, bury their tormentors they find alive. Then they are herded into other camps as the Allies try to devise policy to control the situation. A young poet who cannot quite find himself in this new situation, meets a headstrong Jewish young girl who wants him to run off with her, to the West. He cannot cope with her growing demands for affection, while still harboring the hatred for the Germans and disdain for his fellow men who quickly revert to petty enmities.","popularity":0.2423,"poster_path":"/lFsScY7HSj3PRsflDextkvrtxcq.jpg","production_companies":[{"id":115400,"logo_path":null,"name":"Zespół Filmowy \"Wektor\"","origin_country":"PL"}],"production_countries":[{"iso_3166_1":"PL","name":"Poland"}],"release_date":"1970-08-09","revenue":0,"runtime":109,"softcore":false,"spoken_languages":[{"english_name":"English","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English"},{"english_name":"Polish","iso_639_1":"pl","name":"Polski"}],"status":"Released","tagline":"","title":"Landscape After Battle","video":false,"vote_average":5.886,"vote_count":22,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","title":"Landscape After Battle","type":""},{"iso_3166_1":"NO","title":"Landskap etter krig","type":""}]}}